60
00:03:07.487 --> 00:03:10.223 line:-1 position:50%
[CHIME]
over the animation.


61
00:03:10,223 --> 00:03:12,259 line:-1
The Mac will then
connect to the internet


62
00:03:12,259 --> 00:03:16,563 line:-1
and add itself
to your organization.


63
00:03:16,563 --> 00:03:20,400 line:-1
Version 1.0.1 brought new,
explicit support


64
00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:22.936 line:-1 position:50%
for taking advantage
of existing network connectivity


65
00:03:22,936 --> 00:03:24,638 line:-1
if available on the Mac.


66
00:03:24,638 --> 00:03:31,111 line:-1
And we are excited to announce
that with iOS and iPadOS 16,


67
00:03:31,111 --> 00:03:34,247 line:-1
Apple Configurator for iPhone
can now also add


68
00:03:34,247 --> 00:03:38,919 line:-1
iPhone and iPad devices
to your organization.


69
00:03:38.919 --> 00:03:43.290 line:-1 position:50%
This works just as you expect,
just like adding a Mac.


70
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:46,126 line:-1
